# Plaid × Workhorse slides — Cursor rule

**Hybrid skill (canonical):** [`.claude/skills/plaid-workhorse-slides/SKILL.md`](../../.claude/skills/plaid-workhorse-slides/SKILL.md)

**Workhorse layouts:** [`.claude/skills/tosea-slide-workhorse/`](../../.claude/skills/tosea-slide-workhorse/)

**Plaid brand (always wins):** [`.claude/skills/plaid-slide-design/SKILL.md`](../../.claude/skills/plaid-slide-design/SKILL.md)

## Summary

1. Pick **Workhorse layout** at runtime (`data-workhorse-layout`) from `templates/single-page/`.
2. Wrap in **Plaid shell** (`.frame`, chrome, `data-slide-template="T#"` alias).
3. **Never** use Workhorse themes, `runtime.js`, animations, or Chart.js in pipeline slides.
4. Pipeline loader merges both skills in [`slide-design-skill.js`](../../scripts/scratch/utils/slide-design-skill.js).
